[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bradley Hudson-Odoi: Maidstone sign Sutton forward on loan

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Maidstone United have signed Bradley Hudson-Odoi from National League rivals Sutton United on a one-month loan deal.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The forward, 27, has scored one goal in seven league appearances since moving to Gander Green Lane in the summer.
After spending time in the youth ranks at Fulham, Hudson-Odoi has since had spells at Hereford, Histon, Metropolitan Police and Wealdstone.
He could make his debut for the Stones, who are 16th in the table, at Southport on Saturday.
